<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-06-14T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-06-14T22:00:00-05:00" n="41" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d41">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 EAC/198: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-14T23:00:00-04:00">June 14,
                                    1944—11 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>4729. We welcome the information set forth in your Comea 61 (Embassy’s
                            4655 of June 10).<note n="31" xml:id="d41fn31">
                                <hi rend="italic">Post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_233">p.
                                233</ref>.</note> With respect to the question of consultation with
                            other Allied Governments, we very much hope for definite recommendations
                            at an early date, particularly in view of the developments reported in
                            Schoenfeld’s Nater [<hi rend="italic">Neter</hi>] 11, June 10, 4 p.m.
                            Department’s views on consultation were explained in its 374T of May 10,
                            9 p.m.<note n="32" xml:id="d41fn32">Not printed; it reported on the
                                British Embassy’s <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> of April 15,
                                    <ref target="#pg_54">p. 54</ref>, and the Department’s reply of
                                May 9, <ref target="#pg_56">p. 56</ref>.</note> and its instruction
                            4067 of May 13.<note n="33" xml:id="d41fn33">See footnote 24, <ref target="#pg_57">p. 57</ref>.</note>
                        </p>
                        <p>Please keep Schoenfeld as well as the Department fully informed of all
                            developments on this subject.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>